title: Saleem Rehman wins NA-3 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Saleem Rehman has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-3 Swat-II by securing 81,411 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Wajid Ali Khan of Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz who bagged 27,861 votes.
Votersâ€™ turnout remained 36.1 percent.
